Paper: hep-th/9308053

Date: 1993-08-11

Title: Spontaneous Polarization of the $\Bbb Z _{n}$-Baxter Model

Authors: Yas-Hiro Quano

Comments: 14p, RIMS-930

Journal-ref: Mod. Phys. Lett. A8 (1993) 3363-3376

We show that correlation functions of the $\bz _n $-Baxter model in theprincipal regime satisfy a system of difference equations. We obtain thespontaneous polarization of the $\bz _n $-Baxter model as a solution of thesimplest difference equation.